&lt;p&gt; ;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12860343" author="pradeepkth" created="Fri, 23 Apr 2010 18:31:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unlinking this from 0.7 release and moving to 0.8 since there is a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12898998" author="nrai" created="Mon, 16 Aug 2010 17:26:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have run the test manually and all the tests have been successful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899002" author="rding" created="Mon, 16 Aug 2010 17:39:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The parser bug is fixed, but encounters another problem which is tracked by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1545&quot; title=&quot;Secondary alias gives problem, when it has alias in the group by statement.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1545&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1545&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The work around is to disable the secondary key optimization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch is committed to the trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899003" author="rding" created="Mon, 16 Aug 2010 17:41:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Niraj for fixing this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
